  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency assistance to the slum dwellers affected by fire incident in Dhaka</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A. Multi-purpose cash grant given to 1000 households, 5000 people
B. Hygiene kits given to 1000 households, 5000 people
C. Emergency water supply to 2000 households, 10,000 people                                  
D. Hygiene promotion campaign targeting 5000 people</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project has been designed based on the results of our rapid needs assessment, which allowed the community to provide input into the assistance that they receive. Christian Aid and DAM&#x2019;s response will address food security, shelter and other NFI through MPCGs and WASH supplies as these are the primary humanitarian needs in the affected areas. Our partner DAM has existing programmes in the slum areas of Mirpur and we have already initiated our primary assessment and are pre-positioning stocks.</narrative>
  </description>
